Badger is a CLI tool which can perform certain operations on Badger
databases:
- Backup Badger database to a file in a version-agnostic manner.
- Run bank test on Badger.
- Benchmark Badger for different usecases.
- Generate the autocompletion script for badger for the specified
shell.
- Compact all the LSM tables into one level.
- Print information about the badger key-value store.
- Restore Badger database from a file.
- Rotate the old key with new encryption key.
- Stream the contents of this DB into another DB with the given
options.
